Inspection of the equipment shall include checks that â€”
(a) conductors are securely held in terminals of fittings and are not subject to tension at the terminations;
(b) electrical equipment is adequately supported and secured;
(c) electrical equipment is designed for the environment in which it is located or is suitably enclosed;
(d) lamps do not exceed the rating of the fittings in which they are installed; and
(e) fittings are undamaged and serviceable. If fittings show evidence of overheating, the condition of the wiring shall be checked.
